      "message": "Shouldn\u0027t you abandon the execute if the prepare failed?\n\nAlso, is a warning if the build wasn\u0027t found in the table appropriate?\n\nSomething along the lines of (untested):\n\nmy $sth \u003d $db-\u003eprepare(\u0027SELECT sum(errors), sum(warnings) FROM builds WHERE revision\u003d?\u0027);\nif ($sth) {\n    if ($sth-\u003eexecute($db-\u003equote($buildround)) {\n        my ($errors,$warnings) \u003d $sth-\u003efetchrow_array();\n        if ($errors or $warnings) {\n            message sprintf(\n                \u0027Revision %s result: %d errors, %d warnings (%s committed)\u0027,\n                $buildround, $errors, $warnings, $author\n            );\n        } else {\n            message sprintf(\n                \u0027Revision %s result: All green\u0027, $buildround\n            );\n        }\n    } else {\n        warn \u0027Unable to find build row from revision\u003d\u0027 . $buildround;\n    }\n} else {\n    warn \"DBI: Can\u0027t prepare statement: \". $db-\u003eerrstr;\n}",
